ROLE: IMPLEMENTER
MODE: Local repo on Mac. Electron Desktop UI already implemented and verified.
TASK: Implement Phase 1.5 — UX Acceleration for Review workflow.
SCOPE: UI + IPC + small DB queries only. No pipeline or OAuth changes.

GOAL
Make Review fast, keyboard-driven, and low-friction:
- Keyboard shortcuts
- Approve & Next
- Vendor auto-fill
- Batch approve

FILES TO MODIFY (EXPECTED)
/desktop/renderer/src/pages/ReviewList.tsx
/desktop/renderer/src/pages/ReviewDetail.tsx
/desktop/renderer/src/components/Table.tsx
/desktop/renderer/src/components/ConfirmDialog.tsx
/desktop/renderer/src/state/store.ts
/desktop/main/ipc.ts
/desktop/shared/ipcTypes.ts
/src/app/operations.ts (or equivalent DB wrappers)

FEATURES TO IMPLEMENT

1) Keyboard Shortcuts (Review Detail)
Active only when focus is NOT in an input.
Keys:
- 1 → set status EXPENSE
- 2 → set status TO_REVIEW
- 3 → set status NOT_EXPENSE
- Enter → Save + Next
- j → Next item
- k → Previous item
- o → Open first evidence
- f → Reveal first evidence in Finder
- esc → Back to Review List
Add a small footer hint listing shortcuts.

2) Approve & Next
- Saving a decision automatically navigates to the next item
- “Next” respects current filter + date range
- If no next item, show toast: “All items reviewed”
IPC:
- add getNextReviewItem(currentId, range, filter)

3) Vendor Auto-fill
When loading Review Detail:
- Pre-fill vendor/category if a previous decision exists for:
  - Same sender domain OR
  - Same normalized vendor
- Never auto-save
- User override replaces suggestion
IPC:
- add getSuggestedDecision(messageId)

4) Batch Approve (Review List)
- Enable row selection (checkboxes)
- Show batch toolbar when ≥1 selected
- Batch action dialog:
  - Status (required)
  - Vendor override (optional)
  - Category (optional)
- Confirmation dialog before applying
IPC:
- add applyBatchDecision(messageIds[], decision)

SAFETY & UX RULES
- No silent mass updates
- Always show confirmation for batch
- No secrets in logs
- Renderer must not access DB directly

DEFINITION OF DONE
- Keyboard-only review is possible
- Single-item review is one keystroke + Enter
- Vendor auto-fill reduces typing
- Batch approve works and is confirmed
- No regression to scan/export/auth
- npm run desktop:dev works
- No console errors

OUTPUT FORMAT
Return a single unified diff patch (git patch). No extra commentary.

